using namespace std;

int main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
    int t;
    int ar[4],br[4];
    scanf("%d",&t);
    while(t--)
     {
              //printf("\nenter the coordinates of first and second ie 8 inputs");
              int a,b,c,d,e,f,g,h;
              scanf("%d %d %d %d %d %d %d %d ",&a,&b,&c,&d,&e,&f,&g,&h);
              if(a==e&&b==f&&d==h&&c==g)
               {
                                        printf("%d %d %d %d\n",a,b,c,d);//completely overlap
               }
              else
               {
                    if(   ((e>=a&&e<=c)||(g>=a&&g<=c))&&((f>=b&&f<=d)||(h>=b&&h<=d))   )
                     {
                          ar[0]=a,ar[1]=c,ar[2]=e,ar[3]=g;
                          br[0]=b,br[1]=d,br[2]=f,br[3]=h;
                          sort(ar,ar+4);
                          sort(br,br+4);
                          printf("%d %d %d %d\n",ar[1],br[1],ar[2],br[2]);
                     }
                    else
                     {
                          printf("No Overlap\n");
                     }
               }
     }
    //getch();
    return 0;
}
